Class AbstractDepthPort

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.scufl2.api.common.AbstractCloneable

        • org.apache.taverna.scufl2.api.port.AbstractDepthPort
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable, Named, WorkflowBean, DepthPort, Port
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractGranularDepthPort, InputActivityPort, InputProcessorPort, InputWorkflowPort

    public abstract class AbstractDepthPort
extends AbstractNamed
implements DepthPort
    Abstract implementation of a Port that has a depth property.

    The depth of a Port specifies whether the data is a list and how deep lists are nested. A depth of 0 is a single element, depth 1 is a list, depth 2 is a list of lists and so on.

    Author:
    Alan R Williams
